NFS

Network File System (NFS) is a network file system protocol originally developed by Sun Microsystems in 1984,
allowing a user on a client computer to access files over a network in a manner similar to how local storage is accessed. 

==== Install & Start

1. Server

$ sudo aptitude install nfs-kernel-server

$ sudo vi /etc/exports
/home/zhongxia/nfsshare 172.16.0.*(rw,sync,no_root_squash)

$ sudo service portmap start
start: Job is already running: portmap
$ sudo /etc/init.d/nfs-kernel-server restart 

$ showmount -e localhost
/home/zhongxia/nfsshare 172.16.0.*


2. Client

$ sudo apt-get install nfs-common (æˆ– nfs-kernel-server)

$ sudo service portmap start

$ mkdir /tmp/nfs
$ sudo mount -t nfs 172.16.0.36:/home/zhongxia/nfsshare /tmp/nfs

